Sure! Here's an updated version of the previous web application that encodes the list items in the URL using Base64-encoded JSON and adds a button to share the URL:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
        <title>Buddhist Wisdom List</title>
        <style>
                body {
                        font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
                        background-color: #f9e7d9;
                }
                h1 {
                        text-align: center;
                        color: #b8860b;
                }
                #wisdomList {
                        margin: 20px auto;
                        width: 400px;
                }
                #addWisdomForm {
                        margin-bottom: 20px;
                }
                #addWisdomInput {
                        width: 300px;
                }
                .wisdom {
                        padding: 5px;
                        margin-bottom: 5px;
                        background-color: #fff;
                        border-radius: 5px;
                        box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
                        position: relative;
                }
                .removeWisdom {
                        position: absolute;
                        top: 5px;
                        right: 5px;
                        cursor: pointer;
                        color: #b8860b;
                        font-weight: bold;
                }
                #shareButton {
                        display: block;
                        margin: 20px auto;
                        padding: 10px;
                        background-color: #b8860b;
                        color: #fff;
                        border: none;
                        border-radius: 5px;
                        cursor: pointer;
                }
        </style>
        <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js"></script>
        <script>
                $(document).ready(function() {
                        // Decode any existing data from the URL
                        var data = decodeURIComponent(window.location.hash.substr(1));
                        if (data) {
                                try {
                                        data = JSON.parse(atob(data));
                                        $.each(data, function(i, wisdom) {
                                                $("#wisdomList").append("<div class='wisdom'>" + wisdom + "<span class='removeWisdom'>X</span></div>");
                                        });
                                } catch (e) {
                                        console.log("Error decoding data from URL:", e);
                                }
                        }

                        // Handle adding new wisdom
                        $("#addWisdomForm").submit(function(event) {
                                event.preventDefault();
                                var wisdom = $("#addWisdomInput").val();
                                if (wisdom !== "") {
                                        $("#wisdomList").append("<div class='wisdom'>" + wisdom + "<span class='removeWisdom'>X</span></div>");
                                        $("#addWisdomInput").val("");
                                        updateURL();
                                }
                        });

                        // Handle removing existing wisdom
                        $("#wisdomList").on("click", ".removeWisdom", function() {
                                $(this).parent().remove();
                                updateURL();
                        });

                        // Handle sharing the URL
                        $("#shareButton").click(function() {
                                var data = [];
                                $("#wisdomList > div").each(function() {
                                        data.push($(this).text());
                                });
                                data = btoa(JSON.stringify(data));
                                data = encodeURIComponent(data);
                                var url = window.location.href.split("#")[0] + "#" + data;
                                navigator.clipboard.writeText(url).then(function() {
                                        alert("URL copied to clipboard!");
                                }, function(err) {
                                        console.error("Error copying URL to clipboard:", err);
                                });
                        });

                        // Update the URL when the list changes
                        function updateURL() {
                                var data = [];
                                $("#wisdomList > div").each(function() {
                                        data.push($(this).text());
                                });
                                data = btoa(JSON.stringify(data));
                                data = encodeURIComponent(data);
                                window.history.replaceState(null, null, "#" + data);
                        }
                });
        </script>
</head>
<body>
        <h1>Buddhist Wisdom List</h1>
        <form id="addWisdomForm">
                <input type="text" id="addWisdomInput" placeholder="Enter some wisdom...">
                <button type="submit">Add Wisdom</button>
        </form>
        <div id="wisdomList">
                <!-- Wisdoms will be added here -->
        </div>
        <button id="shareButton">Share URL</button>
</body>
</html>
```

In this version, I've added a button to share the URL of the current list. When the button is clicked, the list items are encoded in the URL using Base64-encoded JSON and copied to the clipboard using the `navigator.clipboard` API. I've also added a function called `updateURL()` that updates the URL whenever the list changes, so that the URL always reflects the current state of the list. Note that this implementation only works for URLs within the same origin due to security restrictions imposed by modern browsers. If you need to share the URL across different origins, you'll need to implement a server-side solution to handle the encoding and decoding of the list items.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
        <title>Buddhist Wisdom List</title>
        <style>
                body {
                        font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
                        background-color: #f9e7d9;
                }
                h1 {
                        text-align: center;
                        color: #b8860b;
                }
                #wisdomList {
                        margin: 20px auto;
                        width: 400px;
                }
                #addWisdomForm {
                        margin-bottom: 20px;
                }
                #addWisdomInput {
                        width: 300px;
                }
                .wisdom {
                        padding: 5px;
                        margin-bottom: 5px;
                        background-color: #fff;
                        border-radius: 5px;
                        box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
                        position: relative;
                }
                .removeWisdom {
                        position: absolute;
                        top: 5px;
                        right: 5px;
                        cursor: pointer;
                        color: #b8860b;
                        font-weight: bold;
                }
                #shareButton {
                        display: block;
                        margin: 20px auto;
                        padding: 10px;
                        background-color: #b8860b;
                        color: #fff;
                        border: none;
                        border-radius: 5px;
                        cursor: pointer;
                }
        </style>
        <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js"></script>
        <script>
                $(document).ready(function() {
                        // Decode any existing data from the URL
                        var data = decodeURIComponent(window.location.hash.substr(1));
                        if (data) {
                                try {
                                        data = JSON.parse(atob(data));
                                        $.each(data, function(i, wisdom) {
                                                $("#wisdomList").append("<div class='wisdom'>" + wisdom + "<span class='removeWisdom'>X</span></div>");
                                        });
                                } catch (e) {
                                        console.log("Error decoding data from URL:", e);
                                }
                        }

                        // Handle adding new wisdom
                        $("#addWisdomForm").submit(function(event) {
                                event.preventDefault();
                                var wisdom = $("#addWisdomInput").val();
                                if (wisdom !== "") {
                                        $("#wisdomList").append("<div class='wisdom'>" + wisdom + "<span class='removeWisdom'>X</span></div>");
                                        $("#addWisdomInput").val("");
                                        updateURL();
                                }
                        });

                        // Handle removing existing wisdom
                        $("#wisdomList").on("click", ".removeWisdom", function() {
                                $(this).parent().remove();
                                updateURL();
                        });

                        // Handle sharing the URL
                        $("#shareButton").click(function() {
                                var data = [];
                                $("#wisdomList > div").each(function() {
                                        data.push($(this).clone().children().remove().end().text());
                                });
                                data = btoa(JSON.stringify(data));
                                data = encodeURIComponent(data);
                                var url = window.location.href.split("#")[0] + "#" + data;
                                navigator.clipboard.writeText(url).then(function() {
                                        alert("URL copied to clipboard!");
                                }, function(err) {
                                        console.error("Error copying URL to clipboard:", err);
                                });
                        });

                        // Update the URL when the list changes
                        function updateURL() {
                                var data = [];
                                $("#wisdomList > div").each(function() {
                                        data.push($(this).clone().children().remove().end().text());
                                });
                                data = btoa(JSON.stringify(data));
                                data = encodeURIComponent(data);
                                window.history.replaceState(null, null, "#" + data);
                        }
                });
        </script>
</head>
<body>
        <h1>Buddhist Wisdom List</h1>
        <form id="addWisdomForm">
                <input type="text" id="addWisdomInput" placeholder="Enter some wisdom...">
                <button type="submit">Add Wisdom</button>
        </form>
        <div id="wisdomList">
                <!-- Wisdoms will be added here -->
        </div>
        <button id="shareButton">Share URL</button>
</body>
</html>
```

The key change is in the `updateURL` and `shareButton` click handler functions. Instead of using `$(this).text()`, which includes the text of the remove button, I'm now using  `$(this).clone().children().remove().end().text()`.

*   `$(this).clone()`: Creates a copy of the wisdom element.
*   `.children().remove()`: Removes all the children of the cloned element (which includes the remove button).
*   `.end()`: Returns the jQuery object back to the cloned wisdom element.
*   `.text()`: Gets the text of the cloned wisdom element, which now only includes the wisdom text itself.

This ensures that only the wisdom text is included when generating the URL.
